    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, transfer it to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray (skin side up) and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Texas-style dalmatian chicken</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining grated garlic</strong> with the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>butter</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>garlic butter</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half, then spread the <strong>garlic butter </strong>over the <strong>ciabatta halves </strong>(reserve the bowl)</p>",
