    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is almost done, add the <strong>ciabatta halves</strong> to a separate <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray and put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until crusty – this is your<strong> Texas-style toast</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>shredded red cabbage </strong>to the reserved bowl with your <strong>mayo </strong>and 1/3 of the <strong>pickling liquid </strong>from the quick-pickled cucumber</p><p>Season with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix everything together – this is your <strong>slaw</strong></p>",
